Let's explore how data is organized and displayed in R and Python! We will first introduce the basic concepts – at the end of each section you will find a quiz to practise.

::: {.lang-r}

## 1 – Simple Variables

As you have already seen, values can be assigned to variables. For the assignment, `<-` and `=` are equivalent:

```{shinylive-r}
#| standalone: true
#| viewerHeight: 220
library(shiny)
CHUNK_ID <- "w1_c1"
ui <- fluidPage(
  textAreaInput("code", "Assignments", value = "a <- 2\nb <- TRUE\n# or:\nb = TRUE\nname = 'Rosalinde'", width = '100%', height = '120px'),
  actionButton("run", "Run Code", class = "btn-success"),
  verbatimTextOutput("out")
)
server <- function(input, output, session) {
  observeEvent(input$run, {
    session$sendCustomMessage("chunkRun", list(chunkId = CHUNK_ID))
    output$out <- renderPrint({
      exprs <- parse(text = input$code)
      for (e in exprs) { res <- withVisible(eval(e)); if (!is.null(res$value) && res$visible) print(res$value) }
    })
  })
}
shinyApp(ui, server)
```

```{=html}
<script>
(function() {
  // Inject postMessage handler into every shinylive iframe on this page
  // We use a MutationObserver to catch iframes as they are added by shinylive
  function injectIntoIframe(iframe) {
    iframe.addEventListener('load', function() {
      try {
        // The shinylive app uses Shiny's custom message handler; we add a
        // window-level listener inside the iframe that forwards to the parent.
        var script = iframe.contentDocument.createElement('script');
        script.textContent = [
          'if (!window.__chunkListenerAdded) {',
          '  window.__chunkListenerAdded = true;',
          '  Shiny.addCustomMessageHandler("chunkRun", function(data) {',
          '    window.parent.postMessage({ type: "chunkDone", chunkId: data.chunkId }, "*");',
          '  });',
          '}'
        ].join('\n');
        iframe.contentDocument.head.appendChild(script);
      } catch(e) {}
    });
  }
  var observer = new MutationObserver(function(mutations) {
    mutations.forEach(function(m) {
      m.addedNodes.forEach(function(node) {
        if (node.tagName === 'IFRAME') injectIntoIframe(node);
        if (node.querySelectorAll) node.querySelectorAll('iframe').forEach(injectIntoIframe);
      });
    });
  });
  observer.observe(document.body, { childList: true, subtree: true });
  // Also handle already-present iframes
  document.querySelectorAll('iframe').forEach(injectIntoIframe);
})();
</script>
```

The function `str()` shows you the **structure** of a variable – `chr` stands for *character* (string), not for chromosomes!

```{shinylive-r}
